<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>We´d like to compare two dates with Zend_Date method compareDate. compareDate calls the _date method. This method extracts a date with the format ‚d.M.Y' when an instance of Zend_Date is given. The problem is, this extraction makes for the overgiven date 01.01.2010 the date 1.1.2009.</p>

<pre class="literal">
$dateValue = new Zend_Date(‚01.01.2010');
$today = new Zend_Date();
$tomorrow = $today-&gt;addDay(1);

$tomorrow-&gt;compareDate($dateValue)  // results 1, when -1 expected
</pre>

